# nextjs/google-font-display <Badge type="info" text="Correctness" />
<div class="rule-meta">
</div>

### What it does

Enforce font-display behavior with Google Fonts.

### Why is this bad?

Specifying display=optional minimizes the risk of invisible text or
layout shift. If swapping to the custom font after it has loaded is
important to you, then use `display=swap`` instead.

### Examples

Examples of **incorrect** code for this rule:
```jsx
import Head from "next/head";

export default Test = () => {
    return (
        <Head>
            <link
                href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Krona+One"
                rel="stylesheet"
            />
        </Head>
    );
};
```

Examples of **correct** code for this rule:
```jsx
import Head from "next/head";

export default Test = () => {
    return (
        <Head>
            <link
                href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Krona+One&display=optional"
                rel="stylesheet"
            />
        </Head>
    );
};
```


## How to use

To **enable** this rule using the config file or in the CLI, you can use:

::: code-group

```json [Config (.oxlintrc.json)]
{
    "plugins": ["nextjs"],
    "rules": {
        "nextjs/google-font-display": "error"
    }
}
```

```bash [CLI]
oxlint --deny nextjs/google-font-display --nextjs-plugin
```

:::


